                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/113: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-21T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 21, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Reference your No. 38 of May 14, noon. The Austrian Foreign Office may be
                    informed that you are prepared to proceed with the exchange of ratifications.
                    The question of leaving a note with the Foreign Office at the same time, in
                    accordance with instruction No. 72 of April 30, has been reconsidered by the
                    Department. You are authorized to exchange ratifications without presenting any
                    note at all, and therefore to cancel the note contained in instruction No.
                    72.</p>
                <p>Department desires to know when exchange of ratifications will take place.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
